---
import ImageSection from "@components/sections/ImageSection.astro";
import IntroSection from "@components/sections/IntroSection.astro";
import Picture from "@components/ui/picture/Picture.astro";
import Heading from "@components/ui/typography/heading/Heading.astro";
import { HeadingSize } from "@components/ui/typography/heading/Heading.models";
import Intro from "@components/ui/typography/intro/Intro.astro";
import image1 from "@images/our-story/apartment-interior.jpg";
import image2 from "@images/our-story/kitchen.jpg";
import image3 from "@images/our-story/staircase.jpg";
import image4 from "@images/our-story/kitchen-2.jpg";
---

<IntroSection>
  <Heading size={HeadingSize.H2}>Architecture as an Extension of Self</Heading>
  <Intro>
    Designing with Purpose: Spaces That Promote Health, Inspire Creativity, and
    Enhance Well-being and Relaxation.
  </Intro>
</IntroSection>

<ImageSection>
  <Picture
    slot="image"
    mainImage={image1}
    alt="Kitchen with carved stone peninsula, dark wooden bar stools, 'Girl with a Pearl Earring' painting, and an old brick ceiling."
  />
  <Fragment slot="body">
    <Heading size={HeadingSize.H3}> Foundations of Wellness </Heading>
    <Intro> Building Health into Every Corner </Intro>
    <p>
      Our designs are centered on health, integrating natural light, clean air,
      and green spaces to encourage a healthy lifestyle. Each project is a step
      towards a world where buildings help us thrive physically and mentally.
    </p>
  </Fragment>
</ImageSection>

<ImageSection>
  <Picture
    slot="image"
    mainImage={image2}
    alt="Captured here is a portion of a kitchen that bears the mark of Skala Studio's expertise. With green cabinets, a travertine stone and brass sheet-backed kitchen island, and an arched utility door, the space exudes sophistication. Ample natural light pours in through the window, creating a welcoming atmosphere that combines style and functionality seamlessly."
  />
  <Fragment slot="body">
    <Heading size={HeadingSize.H3}> Peaceful Spaces by Design </Heading>
    <Intro> Designing Spaces for Quietude and Focus </Intro>
    <p>
      Our approach integrates architectural elements that promote silence and
      focus, essential in todayâ€™s fast-paced world. Utilizing sound-absorbing
      materials, strategic layouts, and calming aesthetics, we create
      environments where individuals can unwind, focus, and find personal peace.
    </p>
  </Fragment>
</ImageSection>
<ImageSection>
  <Picture
    slot="image"
    mainImage={image3}
    alt="A vibrant yellow stair railing against a minimalist blue and white background."
  />
  <Fragment slot="body">
    <Heading size={HeadingSize.H3}> Spaces That Spark Imagination </Heading>
    <Intro> Designing for Innovation and Play </Intro>
    <p>
      Our designs are conceived to invigorate and inspire, creating environments
      that nurture innovation and playful exploration. By integrating flexible
      layouts and through the use of colour, we aim to foster environments where
      creativity flourishes and every space invites discovery and
      experimentation.
    </p>
  </Fragment>
</ImageSection>

<ImageSection>
  <Picture
    slot="image"
    mainImage={image4}
    alt="Industrial style kitchen with white quartz countertops, black cbainets with copper handles. Brick back wall with visible bulb wall lights and large vintage yellow clock. There is a kitchen island with black large pendant light above and a kitchen hob. "
  />
  <Fragment slot="body">
    <Heading size={HeadingSize.H3}> Identity and Architecture </Heading>
    <Intro> Spaces for Individual Narratives </Intro>
    <p>
      Our design process centers on storytelling, using it as a tool to make
      spaces deeply personal, whether they're for one, five, or twenty people.
      We listen to each client's story, translating it into practical,
      meaningful environments. Through this approach, we ensure that every space
      not only serves its function but also connects with its users on a
      personal level.
    </p>
  </Fragment>
</ImageSection>
